      </statement>
    </definition>

      
  
      <remark xml:id="rf-zeros-asymptotes-holes">
        <title>Features of a rational function</title>
       <p>
         Let <m>r(x) = \frac{p(x)}{q(x)}</m> be a rational function.
       </p>
  
       <p>
         <ul>
           <li>
             <p>
               If <m>p(a) = 0</m> and <m>q(a) \ne 0</m>, then <m>r(a) = 0</m>, so <m>r</m> has a zero at <m>x = a</m>.
             </p>
           </li>
           <li>
             <p>
               If <m>q(a) = 0</m> and <m>p(a) \ne 0</m>, then <m>r(a)</m> is undefined and <m>r</m> has a vertical asymptote at <m>x = a</m>.
             </p>
           </li>
           <li>
             <p>
               If <m>p(a) = 0</m> and <m>q(a) = 0</m> and we can show that there is a finite number <m>L</m> such that
               <m>
                 r(x) \to L
               </m>,
               then <m>r(a)</m> is not defined and <m>r</m> has a hole at the point <m>(a,L)</m>.
             </p>
           </li>
         </ul>
       </p>
      </remark>
    
  
    <activity xml:id="activity-rf-matching">
      <introduction>
        <p>Consider the following six graphs of rational functions:</p>
        <sbsgroup>
          <sidebyside width="30%">
            <image>
              <sageplot>
                f(x) = 2*x/(x^2-2*x-8)
                p=plot(f, (x, -7, 7), ymin=-7, ymax=7, color='blue', thickness=3, detect_poles=True)
                p+=parametric_plot((-2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((4,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((x,0),(x,-7,7),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=text('Graph A', (0, 8), fontsize=18, color='black')
                p
              </sageplot>
            </image>
            <image>
              <sageplot>
                f(x) = (x^2+3)/(2*x^2-8)-1
                p=plot(f, (x, -7, 7), ymin=-7, ymax=7, color='blue', thickness=3, detect_poles=True)
                p+=parametric_plot((-2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((x,-1),(x,-7,7),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=text('Graph B', (0, 8), fontsize=18, color='black')
                p
              </sageplot>
            </image>
            <image>
              <sageplot>
                f(x) = 1-(x^2+3)/(2*x^2-8)
                p=plot(f, (x, -7, 7), ymin=-7, ymax=7, color='blue', thickness=3, detect_poles=True)
                p+=parametric_plot((-2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((x,1),(x,-7,7),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=text('Graph C', (0, 8), fontsize=18, color='black')
                p
              </sageplot>
            </image>
          </sidebyside>
          <sidebyside width="30%">
            <image>
              <sageplot>
                f(x) = 2*x/(x^2-2*x-8)-3
                p=plot(f, (x, -7, 7), ymin=-7, ymax=7, color='blue', thickness=3, detect_poles=True)
                p+=parametric_plot((-2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((4,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((x,-3),(x,-7,7),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=text('Graph D', (0, 8), fontsize=18, color='black')
                p
              </sageplot>
            </image>
            <image>
              <sageplot>
                f(x) = (x^2+3)/(2*x^2-8)
                p=plot(f, (x, -7, 7), ymin=-7, ymax=7, color='blue', thickness=3, detect_poles=True)
                p+=parametric_plot((-2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((x,0),(x,-7,7),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=text('Graph E', (0, 8), fontsize=18, color='black')
                p
              </sageplot>
            </image>
            <image>
              <sageplot>
                f(x) = -2*x/(x^2-2*x-8)
                p=plot(f, (x, -7, 7), ymin=-7, ymax=7, color='blue', thickness=3, detect_poles=True)
                p+=parametric_plot((-2,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((4,x),(x,-8,8),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=parametric_plot((x,0),(x,-7,7),color='red',linestyle="--")
                p+=text('Graph F', (0, 8), fontsize=18, color='black')
                p
              </sageplot>
            </image>
          </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <p>Which of the graphs above represents the function <m>f(x)=\frac{2x}{x^2-2x-8}</m>?</p>
      </task>
      <task>
        <p>Which of the graphs above represents the function <m>g(x)=\frac{x^2+3}{2x^2-8}</m>?</p>
      </task>
